cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.OH, cs.IM, cs.MM

This paper involves computer vision techniques to enhance the quality of retinal images acquired using a low-cost direct ophthalmoscope attached to a smartphone camera. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as the images are acquired using a smartphone. Other possible categories include cs.OH (Other Computer Science), cs.IM (Image and Signal Processing), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
